\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
1.
 Purpose
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The purpose of this policy is to establish mandatory standards for the identification,
 classification,
 remediation,
 and mitigation of technical vulnerabilities within Elko County's information systems.
 This policy ensures that security flaws are addressed in a timely manner to prevent exploitation,
 protect the confidentiality,
 integrity,
 and availability of County data (including Criminal Justice Information),
 and maintain compliance with federal and state regulations.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
2.
 Scope
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
This policy applies to all information systems,
 networks,
 hardware,
 software,
 and firmware owned,
 leased,
 operated,
 or managed by Elko County Information Operations.
 This includes servers,
 workstations,
 mobile devices,
 network infrastructure,
 and third-party applications.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
3.
 Roles and Responsibilities
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
IT Director
\series default
:
 Shall serve as the Authorizing Official (AO) for the vulnerability management program and shall approve all Risk Acceptance Memos for vulnerabilities that cannot be remediated within mandated timelines.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Assistant IT Director
\series default
:
 Shall oversee the operational execution of the vulnerability management lifecycle and validate that scanning tools are functioning correctly and reports are generated and reviewed.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
System Administrators
\series default
:
 Shall configure and maintain automated vulnerability scanning tools,
 analyze scan results,
 test patches,
 and implement remediation actions for server and endpoint systems.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Network Administrators
\series default
:
 Shall manage vulnerabilities related to network infrastructure (routers,
 switches,
 firewalls) and remediate identified flaws in firmware or configuration.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Support Specialists
\series default
:
 Shall verify endpoint patch status during support engagements and deployment,
 ensuring antivirus and automated update agents are functional.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Department Heads
\series default
:
 Shall coordinate with Information Operations to schedule maintenance windows for business-critical applications.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
All Personnel
\series default
:
 Shall comply with reboot or update notifications to ensure security patches are applied to assigned workstations.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
4.
 Compliance and Exceptions
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Mandatory Compliance
\series default
:
 Adherence to this policy is mandatory.
 Failure to patch or remediate known vulnerabilities within the specified timelines constitutes a security violation and may result in the quarantine of the non-compliant asset.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
System Isolation
\series default
:
 Systems that cannot be patched and pose a critical risk to the network shall be logically isolated or disconnected until remediation or an approved exception is in place.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Exceptions
\series default
:
 Deviations from remediation timelines or scanning requirements must be documented in a Risk Acceptance Memo in accordance with 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.09"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
 The memo must include technical justification,
 compensating controls,
 and a defined expiration date (not to exceed 12 months).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
CJI Constraints
\series default
:
 Exceptions for systems processing CJI must not violate mandatory FBI CJIS Security Policy requirements without written concurrence from the CJIS Systems Officer (CSO).
\end_layout

