\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.1 Vulnerability Scanning and Identification
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Automated Scanning
\series default
:
 The Department shall employ automated tools to perform authenticated vulnerability scans on all active network assets.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Scanning Frequency
\series default
:
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Internal Systems
\series default
:
 Shall be scanned at least Monthly.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
External-Facing Systems
\series default
:
 Shall be scanned at least Weekly.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
CJI Systems
\series default
:
 Shall be scanned in accordance with the stricter of the County Monthly baseline or CJIS RA-5 requirements.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Ad-Hoc
\series default
:
 Scans shall be initiated within 72 hours of the publication of Critical severity vendor security advisories affecting County assets.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Credentialed Scanning
\series default
:
 To ensure accuracy,
 scans shall be performed using privileged credentials (authenticated scans) whenever technically feasible.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Asset Discovery
\series default
:
 Scanning tools shall be configured to actively discover new or unauthorized devices connected to the network.
\end_layout

